  "prompt": "How can we engage students cognitively?",
  "response": "Here are several strategies to engage students cognitively:\n\n1. Active Learning Techniques\n- Problem-based learning\n- Inquiry-driven instruction\n- Collaborative group work\n- Socratic questioning\n- Discussion-based learning\n\n2. Cognitive Challenge Methods\n- Open-ended questions\n- Complex critical thinking tasks\n- Metacognitive reflection activities\n- Real-world application assignments\n- Multi-step problem-solving challenges\n\n3. Instructional Strategies\n- Connect new information to prior knowledge\n- Use visual and graphic organizers\n- Incorporate interdisciplinary connections\n- Encourage hypothesis generation\n- Promote divergent thinking\n\n4. Technology Integration\n- Interactive digital simulations\n- Online collaborative platforms\n- Gamification of learning\n- Virtual reality experiences\n- Digital research and multimedia projects\n\n5. Cognitive Engagement Principles\n- Create meaningful learning contexts\n- Provide scaffolding and support\n- Offer choice and autonomy\n- Design intellectually stimulating tasks\n- Use formative assessment for feedback\n\n6. Psychological Approaches\n- Foster growth mindset\n- Build intrinsic motivation\n- Develop curiosity\n- Encourage risk-taking\n- Validate student thinking\n\nThese strategies help activate higher-order thinking and deep cognitive processing.",
